            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Between Dec. 2, 1878, and Aug. 14, 1879, Charles Maltby, one-time resident of New Salem, published in the <emph render="italic">Press</emph> of Santa Barbara, Calif. a series entitled &quot;Abraham Lincoln: Personal Recollections of a Good President.&quot;  His articles were then printed (though not without some changes) in <emph render="italic">The Life and Public Services of Abraham Lincoln</emph> (Stockton, Calif.: Independent Steam Power Print, 1884).</p>
                                 <p>Maltby clerked with Lincoln at Denton Offut&#039;s store in New Salem and was later superintendent of Indian affairs in California.</p>
                                 <p>This collection contains microfilm prints of the articles as well as a notice of the series copied into the <emph render="italic">Press</emph> on Dec. 28, 1878, from the <emph render="italic">Los Angeles Express</emph>. The collection was donated to the Library in 2008 by Mark L. Johnson of Springfield, Ill.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


